15/06/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul pledged on Tuesday (14 June) that reforms related to the country's EU membership bid would continue. 
In a speech to a session of a joint EU-Turkey committee, Gul also stressed that the government is committed to pursuing a policy of zero tolerance for human rights violations.
In other news, Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan leaves on Wednesday for an official visit to Lebanon. 
He meets with counterpart Najib Mikati, among others. 
(NTV - 15/06/05; TurkishPress.com, World Bank Web site - 14/06/05)
